headline: 'The end of the UK's tax privilege for non-domiciled residents is an opportunity for France'
description: Other countries are rushing to fill the gap left by the United Kingdom, but not France. According to academics Nizar Atrissi and Ydriss Ziane, France should adopt a genuine strategy to attract private wealth, with clear, stable and competitive rules.

headline: Pier Paolo Pasolini's mysterious death continues to haunt Italy, 50 years on
description: The murder of the Italian writer and filmmaker in 1975 still raises many questions. Among those who have not given up on the case, lawyer Stefano Maccioni hopes a new parliamentary inquiry committee will bring answers.

headline: These French villages have no more drinking water. The reason? PFAS pollution
description: Nearly 3,500 residents across 16 rural villages have been unable to drink tap water since July 10 due to a record-breaking contamination by PFAS, a group of toxic substances known as 'forever chemicals.'
